article.headline: Fidler scores 22, Omaha downs Northern Arizona 81-55
article.description: — Frankie Fidler scored 22 points as Omaha beat Northern Arizona 81-55 on Wednesday night.
article.linkText: Fidler scores 22, Omaha downs Northern Arizona 81-55
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. -- — Frankie Fidler scored 22 points as Omaha beat Northern Arizona 81-55 on Wednesday night. Fidler added five rebounds for the Mavericks (8-8). Tony Osburn added 14 points while shooting 4 for 8 (2 for 6 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free throw line, and also had seven rebounds and three steals. Nick Davis shot 6 of 10 from the field and 1 for 7 from the line to finish with 13 points, while adding eight rebounds. The Lumberjacks (6-8) were led by Oakland Fort, who posted 11 points. Carson Basham added 10 points, six rebounds and two steals for Northern Arizona. Arman Madi also recorded eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
